- Define entities with clear and consistent naming conventions
- Use MikroORM's built-in migrations for database schema management
- Implement soft deletes for entities when applicable
- Use eager loading judiciously to avoid performance issues
- Implement proper transaction management for database operations
- Use MikroORM's query builder for complex queries
- Optimize entity relationships to reduce unnecessary joins